Picture two cheetahs on a racetrack made of price candles. One cheetah is fast and twitchy (the short-term EMA). The other is chill, lumbering, and takes its sweet time (the long-term EMA). When the twitchy cheetah sprints ahead and crosses above the chill one → “BUY, YOU MAGNIFICENT DEGEN!” When the twitchy one gets tired, slows down, and gets lapped from above → “SELL before this turns into a horror movie!”
That, my friend, is the EMA crossover strategy in its purest, most dramatic form.
